reviews.text: Nice market and cheap clothes. You can bargain for a price that you want to pay.
Access from the street is virtually impossible for anyone in a wheelchair.
It mostly offers local and national shows :)
Nice place
Great shows

Pretty good resort with great views. It's pretty close to the marina and the downtown so a good hotel to book if you want to walk to the marina. Staff is really nice and helpful. Food is something to be desired, we found much better food options down the marina. Over all a good place.

Great service, outstanding cleanliness.  Most speak English and Spanish.great effort is taken to ensure you are happy from your morning shower to your perfectly made bed.   Prices are on the "American" level and tipping is appropriate.  A wonderful vacation

Great location with a wonderful staff and amenities.  We own there and glad we do.  Walk to town easily.  The beach is out the back stairs.  Or hang around and be pampered.  Lots of great food within a block.  Highly recommended.

Room was nice but not a very good view. They moved us from one room that you could not see the water to another that you could only see it when standing in one corner of the balcony. We ate at the grill restaurant the first night of our stay and it was so so food, but took almost two hours to order, get the food, and pay the bill, so we didnt eat at any of the other restaurants.
Very nice property. Went her on beach excursion during a recent cruise. Spent several hours here.

The decor, ambiance and service is top notch. Prices are reasonable specially if you compare it on big-city US prices. The food is delicious and very nicely presented. The servings are huge. Highly recommended.
Super great food. Get the guacamole and cheese with their homemade corn tortillas. You can't go wrong!

Fresh and delicious food. Another one of my favorite places to eat in Cabo San Lucas. There is always great entertainment here including music. I enjoy coming here very much and would highly recommend this restaurant for families.
Firat time I ate at Mi Casa was about 27 years ago. The food was fantastic back then, and I think even better now.  Highly recommend!
The atmosphere was awesome! The best mole' I've ever had.  Service is exceptional.  Plus mariachi trio!!
The food and service here is excellent. The owner is hands-on in every aspect of the place, from guest service to food prep. Absolutely wonderful!!

This place is AMAZING!! Everything we have tried here is absolutely phenomenal. The staff is very attentive and the atmosphere is cozy and charming. Highly recommend this place for an excellent dining experience
Fantastic Italian food. Great prices and a hell of a time.
Wonderful place, great food, good prices, excellent service, and very friendly.
Excellent food and service! Highly recommend

The decor, ambiance and service is top notch. Prices are reasonable specially if you compare it on big-city US prices. The food is delicious and very nicely presented. The servings are huge. Highly recommended.
Super great food. Get the guacamole and cheese with their homemade corn tortillas. You can't go wrong!

Firat time I ate at Mi Casa was about 27 years ago. The food was fantastic back then, and I think even better now.  Highly recommend!
The atmosphere was awesome! The best mole' I've ever had.  Service is exceptional.  Plus mariachi trio!!
Really excellent heuvos rancheras, and they were nice enough to mix orange and carrot juice for us.
Always reliably good. Service a lottle slow this time but will still go back for sure
We ate here for brunch because they had a placard sign outside advertising a deal. Quality food! And definitely a great deal for the price. We also enjoyed the open air feel of the place.
Very good, ask for the hot sauce try the res stuff its delicious.
This was the best breakfast we had in Cabo! Only $5...great price,food and service!
Been coming here for 18 years. Food is always great. Sea bass is our favorite! Cheap too. 8 bucks for a full fish dinner. Drinks fairly priced. Great for large groups as restaurant is huge.
Great food! Great service! Support local restaurants like this! :)

Very good local seafood restaurant. Had grilled prawns, tortillas and salsa. Nice atmosphere and good service. Only minor issue was dishes not served with seafood sauce typically included at Mexican seafood restaurants.

We stopped here for drinks and dessert after dinner two nights in a row, great service, friendly waiters, no pushing you to order dinner, they were fine with us just hanging out with our drinks and dessert for a while planning out what to do tomorrow. The restaurant was not at all busy while we were there. Got the elote ice cream the second night, beware that it's big! Delicious but so much corn flavored ice cream, surprisingly delicious and wrapped in a corn husk like a tamale. Liked this place.
Great food at a great price !
We live in Chicago and we love sushi this is by far the best place ever for sashimi we would recommend it for anyone. Definitely five stars rating.
The best experience in Japanese food, best sashimis specifically the specials not on the menu! Excellent service.
Omgoodness!! Better than amazing! We always return to Nick-San in Cabo. Our favorite place.
Excellent service,  friendly staff. Great food!

If you love sushi this is a must do on your vacation.
This is one of my favorite restaurants to go on my trip to Cabo.
I love been surprised by their stylishly way of mixing the Japanese and Mexican cuisine it keeps me coming back for more. Beautiful food!
We've been coming to Cabo for 14 years and this is one of the top 2 or 3 meals we've had. Service excellent food beyond excellent. Atmosphere and music off the charts as well. Definitely coming back.
I always share my catch with the restaurant crew and sample the chefs sauces. Good music,great food and tequila options and service is always good. The crew likes to be there for work and it shows.
It was very very bright in the restaurant we ask for them to turn off the lights. The food was just okay it wasn't very authentic and it was overpriced

Great restaurant in town!! The value is great and their portions are huge. Definitely recommend this place if you want a delicious Mexican meal for a good price. Customer service was excellent and the restaurant is beautifully decorated! We will come back next time we are in Cabo for sure!

By far the best enchiladas I've had in my life. 
I love this place. 
Get the Cadillac margarita.
You're welcome.
